Management career
In the summer of 2006, Ne&lt;U+010D&gt;as took over at Bohemian Football League side FK Bohemians Prague (St&lt;U+0159&gt;&lt;U+00ED&gt;&lt;U+017E&gt;kov), replacing Lubo&lt;U+0161&gt; Urban.13 However his tenure lasted just five matches before he was dismissed, having lost only once during this period.14
Ne&lt;U+010D&gt;as spent some time at Liberec as assistant to manager Ladislav &lt;U+0160&gt;korpil until they were both sacked, along with other assistant coach Lubo&lt;U+0161&gt; Kozel in November 2009.15
Ne&lt;U+010D&gt;as went to Slovakia to manage FK Senica in February 2010 during the 2009&lt;U+2013&gt;10 Slovak Superliga.16 At the beginning of the 2010&lt;U+2013&gt;11 season he went back to the Czech Republic and joined another Bohemian Football League club, this time Arsenal &lt;U+010C&gt;esk&lt;U+00E1&gt; L&lt;U+00ED&gt;pa.17 Having steered the club to mid-table safety, with the club in 11th position with just two games remaining, it was announced that Ne&lt;U+010D&gt;as would leave &lt;U+010C&gt;esk&lt;U+00E1&gt; L&lt;U+00ED&gt;pa at the end of the season.18
In the summer of 2011, Ne&lt;U+010D&gt;as joined Sezimovo &lt;U+00DA&gt;st&lt;U+00ED&gt; in the Czech 2. Liga as assistant manager to Lubo&lt;U+0161&gt; Z&lt;U+00E1&gt;kostelsk&lt;U+00FD&gt;.19
